                "### 2b. Assessing Data - Cek Kualitas Data"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Cek missing values\n",
                "print('=== MISSING VALUES ===')\n",
                "missing = df.isnull().sum()\n",
                "missing_pct = (df.isnull().sum() / len(df) * 100).round(2)\n",
                "missing_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
                "    'Jumlah Missing': missing,\n",
                "    'Persentase (%)': missing_pct\n",
                "})\n",
                "print(missing_df[missing_df['Jumlah Missing'] > 0])"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Cek duplikat\n",
                "print('=== DUPLIKAT ===')\n",
                "print(f'Jumlah baris duplikat: {df.duplicated().sum()}')\n",
                "\n",
                "# Cek tipe data\n",
                "print('\\n=== TIPE DATA ===')\n",
                "print(df.dtypes)"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Cek outlier pada PM2.5 menggunakan IQR\n",
                "print('=== CEK OUTLIER PM2.5 ===')\n",
                "Q1 = df['PM2.5'].quantile(0.25)\n",
                "Q3 = df['PM2.5'].quantile(0.75)\n",
                "IQR = Q3 - Q1\n",
                "lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR\n",
                "upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR\n",
                "\n",
                "outliers = df[(df['PM2.5'] < lower_bound) | (df['PM2.5'] > upper_bound)]\n",
                "print(f'Batas bawah IQR: {lower_bound:.2f}')\n",
                "print(f'Batas atas IQR: {upper_bound:.2f}')\n",
                "print(f'Jumlah outlier PM2.5: {len(outliers)} ({len(outliers)/len(df)*100:.2f}%)')\n",
                "\n",
                "# Visualisasi boxplot\n",
                "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
                "sns.boxplot(y=df['PM2.5'], color='#3498db')\n",
                "plt.title('Boxplot Distribusi PM2.5 - Deteksi Outlier', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
                "plt.ylabel('Konsentrasi PM2.5 (μg/m³)')\n",
                "plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n",
                "plt.tight_layout()\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "> **Insight - Masalah Kualitas Data yang Ditemukan:**\n",
                "> \n",
                "> 1. **Missing Values:** Kolom PM2.5, PM10, SO2, NO2, CO, O3, TEMP, DEWP, RAIN, dan WSPM memiliki data yang hilang. Kolom dengan missing values tertinggi adalah RAIN dengan sekitar {:.2f}% data kosong.\n",
                "> \n",
                "> 2. **Duplikat:** Terdapat {} baris duplikat yang perlu ditangani.\n",
                "> \n",
                "> 3. **Tipe Data:** Kolom 'wd' (wind direction) bertipe object karena berisi arah mata angin, sementara kolom numerik lainnya sudah bertipe int64.\n",
                "> \n",
                "> 4. **Outlier PM2.5:** Ditemukan {} outlier ({:.2f}%) menggunakan metode IQR. Outlier ini kemungkinan adalah kejadian polusi ekstrem yang memang terjadi di Beijing, jadi akan saya pertahankan dalam analisis.".format(\n",">     missing_pct['RAIN'
                ], df.duplicated().sum(), len(outliers), len(outliers)/len(df)*100\n","> )"
            ]
